# 2-sided stationary extension `Ој_в„Ө` (SMB Phase D вҖ” sub-plan)

For a stationary process `(О©, T, Ој, X)` with `X : О© вҶ’ Оұ` (Fintype), this module
builds the canonical 2-sided extension `Ој_в„Ө : Measure (в„Ө вҶ’ Оұ)` such that:

* the natural в„•-projection of `Ој_в„Ө` agrees with the law of `(X вҲҳ T^[i])_{i вүҘ 0}`,
* the shift `Пғ : (в„Ө вҶ’ Оұ) вҶ’ (в„Ө вҶ’ Оұ)`, `Пғ x i := x (i + 1)`, is `Ој_в„Ө`-preserving,
* `Ој_в„Ө` is ergodic whenever `(О©, T, Ој)` is.

The extension is needed because the SMB lower bound (`liminf blockLogAvg вүҘ
entropyRate`) hinges on the *backward* Levy convergence applied to the
Пғ-algebra generated by the negative-time coordinates, which is *not* available
on the one-sided (`в„•`-indexed) side.

See `docs/shannon/smb-two-sided-extension-plan.md` for the full plan, route
choice (HahnвҖ“Kolmogorov on cylinder semiring), and per-phase risks.

